HEADWORD: Boutefeu
<hw>Boute"feu</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.;
<ets>bouter</ets> to thrust, put + <ets>feu</ets> fire.]</ety> <def>An
incendiary; an inciter of quarrels.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Animated by . . . John ⟦agrave⟧ Chamber, a very
<qex>boutefeu</qex>, . . . they entered into open rebellion.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

